verses.verse: To the chief <S%H5329>Musician<s%> on <S%H5058>Neginoth<s%>, A <S%H4210>Psalm<s%> or <S%H7892>Song<s%>. <S%H430>God<s%> be <S%H2603>merciful<s%> unto us, and <S%H1288>bless<s%> us; and cause his <S%H6440>face<s%> to <S%H215>shine<s%> upon us; <S%H5542>Selah<s%>. upon: Heb. with
That thy <S%H1870>way<s%> may be <S%H3045>known<s%> upon <S%H776>earth<s%>, thy saving <S%H3444>health<s%> among all <S%H1471>nations<s%>.
Let the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> thee, O <S%H430>God<s%>; let all the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> thee.

O let the <S%H3816>nations<s%> be <S%H8055>glad<s%> and sing for <S%H7442>joy<s%>: for thou shalt <S%H8199>judge<s%> the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H4334>righteously<s%>, and <S%H5148>govern<s%> the <S%H3816>nations<s%> upon <S%H776>earth<s%>. <S%H5542>Selah<s%>. govern: Heb. lead
Let the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> thee, O <S%H430>God<s%>; let all the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> thee.
Then shall the <S%H776>earth<s%> <S%H5414>yield<s%> her <S%H2981>increase<s%>; and <S%H430>God<s%>, even our own <S%H430>God<s%>, shall <S%H1288>bless<s%> us.
<S%H430>God<s%> shall <S%H1288>bless<s%> us; and all the <S%H657>ends<s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%> shall <S%H3372>fear<s%> him.
